    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-11-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="257"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                <head>257. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    Station in Saigon to the Director of the National Security Agency (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BLGGA1" type="to">Blake</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d257fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, <gloss
                            target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 26 <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> VIET
                        Secret; Flash. The source text is the copy sent for information Flash to the
                        Department of State. Also sent Flash to <gloss target="#t_USIB1"
                            >USIB</gloss> agencies. Received at the Department of State at 3:55
                        a.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1963-11-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1963</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Critic. Conein reports from <gloss target="#t_JGS1">JGS</gloss> that Gens have
                    group of nationalistic anti-Communist pro-Western civilian politicians with them
                    at <gloss target="#t_JGS1">JGS</gloss>. These individuals will head the new
                    civil administration. There well be no military personalities in high positions
                    in the new government. Military hopes to turn over government to the civilians
                    within two to three days.</p>
                <p>Gens have taped a proclamation for broadcast and have taken over VTVN studios.
                    However, one relay point apparently blown up, and broadcast of proclamation
                    delayed.</p>
                <pb facs="0538" n="512" xml:id="pg_512"/>
                <p>Now at <gloss target="#t_JGS1">JGS</gloss> are Gens <persName
                        corresp="#p_DVBMMG1">“Big” Minh</persName> and “Little” Minh, <persName
                        corresp="#p_KHIEM1">Khiem</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_KIM1"
                        >Kim</persName>, <persName>Le</persName>, and Chieu. Gens claim Gen Khanh
                    and Gen Tri also supporting coup. Gens report Bien Hoa and My Tho have been
                    taken by forces loyal to them.</p>
                <p>Now heavy firing vicinity Embassy. <gloss target="#t_AAA1">AAA</gloss> going up.
                    Apparently duel going on between aircraft and ships in river.</p>
            </div>
